// Semantic direction:
// Parquet is a columnar binary format optimized for analytical queries on large datasets.
// parquet_row_group is the primary partitioning unit; row_group_size controls memory during write.
// parquet_column_chunk stores all values for one column in one row group.
// parquet_page is the smallest unit of compression and encoding within a column chunk.
// encoding_rle (Run-Length Encoding) efficiently stores repeated values; encoding_delta stores differences.
// encoding_dict builds a dictionary of unique values and stores indices, reducing size for low-cardinality columns.
// parquet_statistics records column_min, column_max, and column_null_count for row group pruning.
// bloom_filter enables probabilistic membership testing to skip row groups lacking a query value.
// parquet_predicate_pushdown filters row groups and pages before reading data, minimizing I/O.
// column_projection reads only the requested columns rather than the full row.
// Arrow is a columnar in-memory format designed for zero-copy inter-process data sharing.
// validity_bitmap is a bit array where 0 marks null positions in an arrow_array.
// arrow_record_batch is a collection of equal-length arrays sharing one arrow_schema.
// arrow_ipc serializes record batches for network transfer or file storage.
// flight_protocol uses gRPC to transfer Arrow data between services with high throughput.
// arrow_compute provides vectorized compute_functions (sort, filter, aggregate) over arrow_arrays.
// Avro is a schema-based binary format used heavily in event streaming and Hadoop ecosystems.
// avro_schema_registry stores and versions schemas; consumers fetch the schema_id from message headers.
// schema_evolution allows adding optional fields without breaking existing readers.
// avro_union encodes nullable fields as a union of the field type and null.

// Primitive flow:
// Parquet write: schema + rows -> column batches -> row_group
//   per column: encoding_dict or encoding_rle -> compress_zstd -> parquet_page
//   statistics: min/max/null_count per column -> row_group metadata
//   bloom_filter per column -> parquet_write -> .parquet file
// Parquet read: row_group scan -> predicate_pushdown: statistics check -> skip if no match
//   column_projection: read only needed columns -> page decode -> decompress -> values
// Arrow: data -> arrow_record_batch -> ipc_stream_format -> socket/file
//   receiver: ipc_message decode -> arrow_record_batch (zero-copy if same process)
// Avro: avro_schema from schema_registry(schema_id) -> avro_decode(bytes) -> avro_record fields

// This defines Parquet columnar storage with predicate pushdown and bloom filters,
// Arrow zero-copy in-memory format with IPC and Flight, and Avro schema-registry serialization.
